---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTABand from '@/components/CTABand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Disability Insurance | Heidi Blondin Financial"
  description="Your income is your most valuable asset. Disability insurance protects it if illness or injury keeps you from working. Independent advice from Heidi Blondin Financial."
>

  <section class="bg-brand-plum py-20">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-5">Insurance</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-display text-white text-balance" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Disability Insurance</h1>
      <p class="font-sans text-[18px] text-white/65 mt-5 leading-relaxed">
        You insure your home. You insure your car. But your income — the thing that pays for everything — is often left unprotected. Disability insurance changes that.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white section-gap">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-6" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">What disability insurance actually protects</h2>
      <div class="font-sans text-[17px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>Disability insurance replaces a portion of your income — typically 60–70% — if you're unable to work due to illness or injury. This income continues for as long as you remain disabled (up to the policy's benefit period), allowing you to meet your obligations without depleting savings or going into debt.</p>
        <p>The risk is higher than most people assume: according to the Canadian Life and Health Insurance Association, 1 in 3 Canadians will experience a disability lasting 90 days or more before age 65. The most common causes aren't accidents — they're cancer, mental health conditions, and musculoskeletal issues.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Short-term vs. long-term disability</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[13px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">Short-term coverage typically begins quickly (within days) and lasts weeks to months. Long-term disability kicks in after a waiting period (30–120 days) and can continue to age 65. Most working adults need long-term coverage most.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Own-occupation vs. any-occupation</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[13px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">The best policies pay if you can't perform your own specific occupation. "Any occupation" policies only pay if you can't work in any job at all — a much harder standard to meet, and often not what people think they're buying.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Non-cancellable and guaranteed renewable</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[13px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">Premium policies cannot be cancelled or have premiums increased by the insurer as long as you pay your premiums — protecting you if your health changes after you purchase coverage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Group vs. individual coverage</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[13px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">If your employer provides group disability insurance, you may still have coverage gaps — limits on benefit amount, waiting periods, or a definition of disability that doesn't suit your occupation. Individual coverage fills those gaps.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-4" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Who especially needs disability insurance</h2>
        <ul class="font-sans text-[16px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-gold mt-1">→</span><span>Self-employed professionals — no group benefit safety net, income stops completely if you can't work</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-gold mt-1">→</span><span>Primary earners with dependents and a mortgage</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-gold mt-1">→</span><span>Anyone whose employer's group disability plan has gaps or coverage limits</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-gold mt-1">→</span><span>Professionals in skilled occupations whose income depends on specific physical or cognitive abilities</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 bg-brand-tintPlum p-5 border-l-2 border-brand-plum/30">
        <p class="font-sans text-xs text-brand-ink/55 leading-relaxed">Insurance products are offered through Heidi Blondin Financial / Qualified Financial Services. This article is for general information purposes only and does not constitute personalized insurance advice. Please consult with a qualified advisor to determine what coverage is appropriate for your situation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand heading="Protect your income" sub="Book a free consultation and we'll help you understand what disability coverage you actually need." />

</BaseLayout>
